About Me

Who Am I?

Unless you've directly landed here skipping the homepage my name is Aman Kumar (Pronounced "Aam-un Koo-maar"). I am a Front End Web Developer from India. I spend 12 hours a day in front of my computer. 8 hours to code, 2 hours for browse reddit and the rest to play video games. You can call me a workaholic. I love building projects for the web and just programming in general. My source of energy is my willpower, commitment, a little bit of stubbornness and a lot of coffee.

So What Exactly Do I Do?

We already know that I'm a web developer, I build websites and web applications, but does a filmmaker just shoot vidoes? and a photographer just capture images? Well yeah, but my point is, I love my work. I take it very seriously and look at it as a lot more than just sitting on a desk and spewing out code. I don't just build websites, I build Experiences.
